{"meta":{"updateDate":1755117017719,"pPcc":"SAT#P","questionId":"13e5a5d5","skill_cd":"P.B.","score_band_range_cd":2,"skill_desc":"Nonlinear equations in one variable and systems of equations in two variables ","createDate":1755117017719,"program":"SAT","primary_class_cd_desc":"Advanced Math","ibn":"","external_id":"711ce341-6b08-4443-a2bc-e3ddb891f609","primary_class_cd":"P","uId":"46235812-e2ba-4e78-a6b3-4fa8266ca1b1","difficulty":"E"},"source":"modern","detail":{"type":"spr","stem":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><math alttext=\"5 StartAbsoluteValue x EndAbsoluteValue equals 45\"><mrow>\n\t<mrow>\n\t\t<mn>5</mn>\n\t\t<mrow>\n\t\t\t<mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\">\n\t\t\t\t<mi>x</mi>\n\t\t\t</mfenced>\n\t\t</mrow>\n\t</mrow>\n\t<mo>=</mo>\n\t<mn>45</mn>\n</mrow>\n</math></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">What is the positive solution to the given equation?</p>","keys":["9"],"rationale":"<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The correct answer is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"9\"><mn>9</mn></math>. Dividing both sides of the given equation by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"5\"><mn>5</mn></math> yields <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"StartAbsoluteValue x EndAbsoluteValue equals 9\"><mo>|</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>|</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn></math>. By the definition of absolute value, if <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"StartAbsoluteValue x EndAbsoluteValue equals 9\"><mo>|</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>|</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn></math>, then <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x equals 9\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x equals negative 9\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></math>. Therefore, the two solutions to the equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"5 StartAbsoluteValue x EndAbsoluteValue equals 45\"><mn>5</mn><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>45</mn></math> are <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"9\"><mn>9</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"negative 9\"><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></math>.&nbsp;It follows that the positive solution to the given equation is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"9\"><mn>9</mn></math>.</p>","externalid":"711ce341-6b08-4443-a2bc-e3ddb891f609","correct_answer":["9"]}}